                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.263,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 147560,
                                "text": "In case 08-674 NRG Power marketing versus Main Public Utilities Commission, Justice Ginsburg has the opinion of the Court."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.263,
                        "stop": 260.493,
                        "byte_start": 147560,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.263,
                                "stop": 24.861,
                                "byte_start": 147560,
                                "byte_stop": 205970,
                                "text": "The Mobile-Sierra doctrine named for two over half-century old decisions of this court, concerns superintendents of power rate by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.861,
                                "stop": 28.937,
                                "byte_start": 205970,
                                "byte_stop": 222271,
                                "text": "This case is about the dimensions of that doctrine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.937,
                                "stop": 36.482,
                                "byte_start": 222271,
                                "byte_stop": 252468,
                                "text": "When an electricity rate is set by freely negotiated wholesale energy contracts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.482,
                                "stop": 46.962,
                                "byte_start": 252468,
                                "byte_stop": 294369,
                                "text": "Mobile-Sierra instructs, the commission is to presume that the rate qualifies as just reasonable under the Federal Power Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.962,
                                "stop": 56.098,
                                "byte_start": 294369,
                                "byte_stop": 330940,
                                "text": "The presumption may be overcome however, if the commission determines that the contract rate seriously harms the public interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.098,
                                "stop": 63.801,
                                "byte_start": 330940,
                                "byte_stop": 361765,
                                "text": "For many years New England supply of electricity capacity was barely sufficient to meet the region\u0027s demand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.801,
                                "stop": 79.049,
                                "byte_start": 361765,
                                "byte_stop": 422787,
                                "text": "The Federal Commission and New England\u0027s generators, electricity providers and power customers, made several attempts to address the problem, this case stems from the latest effort to design the solution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.049,
                                "stop": 97.467,
                                "byte_start": 422787,
                                "byte_stop": 496452,
                                "text": "Concerned parties negotiated a comprehensive settlement agreement, their accord, which the commission approved, established rate-setting mechanisms, for sales of energy capacity, and provided that the Mobile-Sierra public interest standards would govern rate changes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.467,
                                "stop": 101.811,
                                "byte_start": 496452,
                                "byte_stop": 513797,
                                "text": "Objectors to the settlement sought review in the DC circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.811,
                                "stop": 111.14,
                                "byte_start": 513797,
                                "byte_stop": 551100,
                                "text": "By and large, the Court of Appeals affirmed the commission\u0027s order but it agreed with the objectors on the point here at issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.14,
                                "stop": 123.355,
                                "byte_start": 551100,
                                "byte_stop": 600001,
                                "text": "When the contract rate is challenged by non-cut contacting third parties, the court held, the Mobile-Sierra presumption that the rate is just and reasonable does not apply."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.355,
                                "stop": 125.642,
                                "byte_start": 600001,
                                "byte_stop": 609092,
                                "text": "We reverse that determination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.642,
                                "stop": 137.835,
                                "byte_start": 609092,
                                "byte_stop": 657889,
                                "text": "Mobile-Sierra\u0027s public interest standard we hold, applies to all challenges, to contract rates whether initiated by contracting parties or non contracting parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.835,
                                "stop": 150.625,
                                "byte_start": 657889,
                                "byte_stop": 709089,
                                "text": "For this conclusion, we rely heavily on this court\u0027s 2008 Morgan Stanley decision, which we announced three months after the Court of Appeals ruling in the instant case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.625,
                                "stop": 175.159,
                                "byte_start": 709089,
                                "byte_stop": 807205,
                                "text": "Morgan Stanley makes it unmistakably clear that Mobile-Sierra\u0027s public interest standard is not as the DC Circuit suggested independent of and sometimes at odds with the just-and-reasonable standard, rather the public interest standard defines what it means a rate to satisfy the just-and-reasonable standard in the contract context."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.159,
                                "stop": 196.317,
                                "byte_start": 807205,
                                "byte_stop": 891841,
                                "text": "We state three principal reasons for our opinion, first if the commission itself as adjudicator of great challenges must presume that contract rates resulting from fair arms length negotiations are just unreasonable and how can non-contracting parties escape that presumption."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.317,
                                "stop": 208.343,
                                "byte_start": 891841,
                                "byte_stop": 939907,
                                "text": "Second, Mobile-Sierra as take account of third-party interest where the doctrine directs the commission to reject the contract rate that seriously harms the consuming public."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.343,
                                "stop": 227.211,
                                "byte_start": 939907,
                                "byte_stop": 1015348,
                                "text": "Most critically, the DC circuit\u0027s confinement of Mobile-Sierra to challenges by contracting parties defeats the doctrine\u0027s animating purpose, promotion of the stability of supply arrangements which all agree is essential to the health of the energy industry."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 227.211,
                                "stop": 241.281,
                                "byte_start": 1015348,
                                "byte_stop": 1071668,
                                "text": "A presumption applicable to contracting parties but inapplicable to all others who might challenge a contract rate could scarcely provide the stability Mobile-Sierra aimed to secure."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.281,
                                "stop": 256.917,
                                "byte_start": 1071668,
                                "byte_stop": 1134258,
                                "text": "Whether the rates at issue qualify as contract rates for Mobile-Sierra purposes, and, if not, whether the commission had discretion to treat them analogously, our question is left open for the DC circuit\u0027s consideration on remand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 256.917,
                                "stop": 260.493,
                                "byte_start": 1134258,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
